MC: You used to hum. That same melody, every dusk.
Weaver: Did I?
MC: You did. It was always the same tune.
Weaver: Funny... I never had a voice for music.
MC: ...What?
Weaver: You've filled in too many gaps, dear child.
Weaver: You think grief makes you wiser. But it only softens your memories.
MC: Who are you really?
Weaver: A mirror. A mask. A thread spun from your guilt.
Weaver: And I'm far from the last.
MC: (Damn it...)
